Stories included:

  • Sleep Walk - A man tries to remain friends with an ex partner, but finds that he still loves her. The two meet up on his birthday, but it becomes clear that she is acting out of pity, and has no interest in him. On the way home, he is involved in a minor car accident.
  • Echo Ave. - When a couple choose to spy on the occupants of a nearby apartment, one of them ends up seeing a lot more than they intended.
  • Long Distance - A girl tries to put some spice back into a long distance relationship, but when her boyfriend sends her a risqu√© letter to read back to him over the phone but, she soon realises it may be doing more harm than good.
  • Drop - A single page story about a man who suffers a fall.
  • Lunch Break - This story shows a typical day in the life of a lonely, elderly lady whose memories of her late partner are all she has for company.

Stories included:

  • The Connecting Thread - A woman who is obsessed with personal ads learns a valuable lesson about self-image. She is reading them one morning when she spots an ad which appears to be addressed to her, and when the ads become more frequent, she becomes obsessed with finding out who is behind them.
  • Summer Job - A teen boy gets his first part-time job in a photocopying shop.
  • Pink Frosting - A man is on his way home with a birthday cake to his partner's surprise party when he becomes involved in an accident. He is then subjected to a vicious assault.
  • Layover - A man misses his flight, and wanders around for the night rather than return to the people he is staying with.

Stories included:

  • Dylan and Donovan - A story about twin girls, one of whom is devastated when she reads her sister's diary and uncovers a secret.
  • Supermarket - A blind man goes shopping to his local store, where he appears to share a special friendship with one of the employees.
  • Hostage Situation - A man on a bus journey becomes increasingly anxious about the behaviour of those around him.
  • Unfaded - When a young man is asked to redecorate his grandfather's old house, it triggers strong memories.

Stories included:

  • Six Day Cold - A man comes down with the flu, and is out buying medicine when he runs into his ex girlfriend. She offers to come and take care of him, and the pair find there is still a spark between them.
  • Fourth Of July - A young boy goes for a walk on his own at night, on Independence Day.
  • Hazel Eyes - A young woman tries to start a new life, but discovers that no matter where she goes, she is always herself.

Contains the story "Alter Ego".

Martin Courtney is a writer who is struggling to write the follow up to his debut novel, a semi-autobiographical tale which enjoyed moderate success and acclaim. When he receives a postcard out of the blue from his high school crush, Samantha Kinzel, he decides to try and track her down. He finds that she has moved out of town, and instead strikes up an unexpected friendship with her teenaged sister, Jenna.

Contains the story "Hawaiian Gateway".

After moving away from her family, and the pressure from her parents to be more like her sister Grace, Hillary Chan begins a new life. But everything starts to go wrong when she loses her job in telesales, and falls into a rut. As her life grinds to a halt, she dreams of winning a holiday to a warmer place, far away.

Contains the story "Summer Blonde".

Vanessa is a young, attractive woman with a boyfriend who dotes on her. But when the mysterious and handsome musician Carlos moves into the neighbourhood, her eye begins to wander. Vanessa also has another admirer - a loner named Neil, who has a fondness for spying on his neighbours.

In this issue Tomine tells the story of two outcast teenagers and of the tense undercurrents that exist between them and the more popular group of students at school. This is the story that Dave Eggers chose to be included in the book The Best American Non-Required Reading.

Contains the story "Bomb Scare".

A coming of age tale about two teenage friends, Cammie and Scotty.

First part of a three part story. Continued in issues 10 and 11.

Ben Tanaka and Miko Hayashi's relationship is already strained when Ben develops a worrying obsession.

Second part of a three part story. Continued in issue 11.

After he and Miko decide to take a break, Ben chooses to pursue the one thing he has wanted all along. But his attempts are nowhere near as successful as he had hoped.

"Shortcomings" part 3 of 3

In this long-awaited conclusion to Adrian Tomine's three-part epic, the story leaps across the country, taking place entirely in New York. All of protagonist Ben Tanaka's worst (and most amusing) traits are brought to the fore as his obsessive quest reaches a fever pitch. His best friend, Alice Kim, finds herself at an unexpected crossroads in her life, forcing her to make several life-altering decisions. But whatever happened to Ben's girlfriend, Miko Hayashi? That and many other answers are revealed as our protagonists walk and talk their way through the streets of Brooklyn and Manhattan, all delineated in Tomine's evocatively pristine style.

Final part of a three part story. Continued from issues 9 and 10.

After flying to New York to confront Miko, Ben discovers she has begun a new relationship and is not interested in reconciling. Meanwhile, Alice finds love with a woman named Meredith, and decides to move away from California.

In the new, long-awaited Optic Nerve #12, award-winning Shortcomings cartoonist Adrian Tomine returns to the multiple short story format familiar from early issues of the iconic series and showcases Tomine's trademark humor and observational skill. 'A Brief History of the Art Form Known as Hortisculpture' deftly manipulates traditional comics idioms to tell a story of horticulture, patents, and misunderstood art forms, while 'Amber Sweet' is a disconcertingly modern tale about a case of mistaken identity.

General Notes

The cover is actually not as wide as the comic, and when the book is closed, the cover allows you to partially view the first page of the comic.

name: Water, Water, Everywhere!

description:
Someone has tried to take the life of Iceberg, mayor of Water Seven, and he's blaming Robin for the deed. But Robin has disappeared and left the Straw Hats under a cloud of suspicion! Now the crew members are on the run, looking for a way to clear their names. Could a mysterious group known as CP9 be to blame? Or is Robin really guilty?

Robin has suddenly left the crew, and her true intentions are revealed! There are reasons for her motives, but the crew is puzzled by her dealing with the secret government organization CP9. What will happen to the Strawhats and Robin, and just what is CP9 up to? Luffy will soon find out.
name: 9th Justice

description:
As the true identities of the CP9 assassins are revealed, so is their real motive--to get their hands on the blueprints for the Pluton, the most destructive weapon of the ancient world! With Robin leaving the crew of her own free will, the CP9 won't let anything stand in the way of their mission... least of all the Straw Hats!

After leaving the Straw Hat Pirates, Robin is heading to the naval base, Enies Lobby, with CP9. Her tragic fate is to be executed. Luffy and the crew, however, are in pursuit. Meanwhile, Usopp and Franky meet, and Franky's past is revealed. It also becomes known that Franky holds the secret to a weapon called Pluton. Because the government is seeking this weapon, CP9 also captures Franky and Usopp.
name: Tom

description:
After finding out the real reason for Robin's betrayal, the Straw Hats are in a madcap race to rescue her from CP9, the Navy's elite assassin group. But first they'll have to find a way to sail through the tidal wave known as Aqua Laguna. Will the Rocketman be seaworthy for the task at hand, or will it be a runaway train to catastrophe?!

The Straw Hat crew is vigorously chasing down Robin, trying to reach her before she arrives at Enies Lobby. But can their sea train, Rocket Man, catch up with Robin and CP9's sea train? Many challenges are awaiting them on this chase. The fearsome weather poses a threat, but the CP9 members they'll encounter are much more deadly!
name: Rocketman!

description:
Sanji, Usopp and Franky are on their own against the Navy as the rest of the Straw Hats hurry to catch up to the speeding Sea Train. But freeing Robin from the clutches of CP9 won't be an easy task with a train full of enemies. And even if they do reach her, does she even want to be rescued?!

Luffy and the Straw Hats are preparing to face off against CP9, but there's a lot of struggles they must overcome first. More deadly CP9 agents are also introduced. Robin and CP9 continue to get away, but everyone finally makes it to Enies Lobby.
name: Struggle

description:
Hankering for a fight, Luffy's got a jump start on the battle to rescue Robin and Franky before they're sentenced by the Navy's court at Enies Lobby. Now that the Straw Hats and the Franky Family have banded together, the World Government is in for an epic battle. But did the Navy deceive Robin into sacrificing herself in order to trap the Straw Hats?!

The fight on Enies Lobby has finally begun. The Straw Hats are ready to take back Robin, but CP9 still stands in their way. Luckily, Luffy has a new fearsome technique up his sleeve.
name: Gear

description:
Robin and Franky have been captured by CP9 and locked in the courthouse on Enies Lobby. The Straw Hats and Franky's crew must join forces if they want to save their friends. But before they can rescue them, they must face Spandam's six deadly assassins. Can the two groups work together, or will CP9 finally win?

The Straw Hats and CP9 line-up for their final battle. Robin's tragic past is also revealed. Everyone she ever teams up with suffers death, and to stop that, all she wants is to die herself. Luffy talks her out of it, and she declares her wish to live. Now it's up to Luffy and the crew to fulfill that wish and keep her alive.
name: Declaration of War

description:
The Straw Hats have infiltrated the Tower of Law to save Robin, but they still need a special key to release her. One of the CP9 assassins holds the right key, but Luffy and his crew may have to defeat them all. Can the Straw Hats thwart CP9 and rescue Robin?

The Straw Hat Pirates storm the Judicial Tower in Enies Lobby to engage in the final showdown against CP9. While the crew takes on the agents of CP9, Luffy rushes towards the leader, Rob Lucci.
name: Pirates vs. CP9

description: Luffy has made it to the tower where Robin is being held captive, but in order to save her, he must first get past the deadly assassin Rob Lucci. The rest of the Straw Hats are busy fighting their own battles to find the key that will free Robin. Can the crew find the right key in time?!
name: Legend of a Hero

description: The battle between Luffy and CP9 agent Rob Lucci escalates while the rest of the crew tries to escape to safety through the Gates of Justice. Suddenly, a fleet of warships sent by the Navy Headquarters arrives on the scene and begins bombarding the island. Will the crew get away before the island is blown to smithereens?!
name: Let's Go Back

description: Without a ship to sail, the Straw Hats are grounded for good. Luckily, the inhabitants of Water Seven rally together to help them out to show their appreciation. But the crew will need to set sail quickly when Vice Admiral Garp comes after them. Luffy knows all too well that he won't stand a chance if this fearsome Navy officer catches him!
name: You Have My Sympathies

description: When the Straw Hats encounter a mysterious barrel on the open sea, little do they know that it's a trap. Losing control of their ship, they're steered toward Thriller Bark. Any rational sailor would think twice before going ashore on an island full of zombies. But with Luffy at the helm, the Straw Hats are in for a scare as they become the targets of the dreaded Gecko Moria!
name: Adventure on Ghost Island

description: The Straw Hats find themselves caught in the Florian Triangle when the mysterious island "Thriller Bark" suddenly appears. Gecko Moria, one of the Seven Warlords, and his zombie army are also on the island, and they're preparing for a Night Hunt! Can the Straw Hat crew survive this fearsome evening?
name: Cloudy, Partly Bony

description: The Straw Hats rush back into Thriller Bark in an all-out battle with Gecko Moria's Zombie Generals. But Moria has a secret weapon: Oars, a massive zombie warrior who's got all of Luffy's fighting skills! Have the Straw Hats finally met an opponent too powerful to beat?
name: Adventures of Oars

description: In their effort to help their new friend Brook regain his shadow from Gecko Moria and his army of zombies, Luffy, Sanji and Zolo lose their shadows too! A human with no shadow will die if sunlight hits them! Can the crew defeat one of the Seven Warlords of the Sea to get their shadows back before the sun rises?
name: Nightmare Luffy

description: The Straw Hats are in a desperate battle against time and Gecko Moria to get their shadows back before dawn. Gecko Moria unleashes his devastating power of a thousand shadows, but Luffy counters back with his "Gear" powers. To save his crew, will Luffy have to make the ultimate sacrifice?
name: Arriving Again

description: Camie the mermaid offers to take Luffy and the crew to Fish-Man Island if they'll help rescue her boss Hachi from the notorious Flying Fish Riders. Ignoring all of the warning signs (hint: her boss sounds suspiciously like an old enemy!), the crew agrees to help their mermaid friend, only to end up losing Camie to other kidnappers!
name: The Eleven Supernovas

description: In his effort to save Camie the mermaid from being sold to the highest bidder, Luffy's attack on an exalted Celestial Dragon has given the Navy the green light to send the Admirals in after him. But the Straw Hats get help from an unexpected source--a mysterious outlaw who knows all about Gold Roger, the original King of the Pirates!
name: Roger and Rayleigh

description: When the Straw Hats come in contact with Bartholomew Kuma's bare paw, this Warlord of the Sea's teleportation power sends them flying to an unknown location. Luffy lands on a maiden island where he battles the local Amazons. But with the crew scattered all around the world, will they ever be able to meet up again?!
name: Natural Born King

description: With his brother Ace locked up in the Naval prison Impel Down, Luffy doesn't have much time to rescue him before his imminent execution. While he may have found a way to sneak into the maximum-security prison, finding Ace isn't going to be as easy. But a chance reunion with some former enemies just might be a blessing in disguise!
name: Unstoppable

description: Luffy's got some backup in his former enemies Buggy the Clown, Mr. 2 Bon Clay and Mr. 3 as he tries to rescue his brother from Impel Down prison. But now Warden Magellan, with his Venom-Venom powers, is out to stop him! Can Luffy survive such a dangerous attack from a person whose very breath is a deadly weapon, or could his ace in the hole possibly be a "queen"?
name: A Ray of Hope

description:
Thank You

With Ivankov's help, Luffy now struggles to make his way back out of Impel Down in order to prevent the execution of his brother Ace. All the prisoners will have to work together if they ever hope to get past the dangerous Warden Magellan. But will an earth-shattering proclamation by the World Government turn everything upside down?

With Whitebeard injured, the Navy launches a counterstrike to finish the pirate rebellion once and for all. And as the three Navy Admirals stand in his way, Luffy will need one last trick if he hopes to save his brother Ace from being executed.

description: Things just can't get any worse for Antonio Mercer. A private eye by trade, a dame from his past has resurfaced in his life as a client - along with all of the emotional baggage he thought he'd left behind forever. Of course, this unusual client doesn't have just any case; her family is mixed up with seriously dangerous people, and the body count is just starting to pile up!
name: HC

description: The hit new ongoing series from Image is collected! In a dark future ruled by the Murder Messiah, street witch Liberty Lochs is on a mission to change the past. Meanwhile, horror heroes Cassie Hack & Vlad must contend with an obsessive serial killer, and a duo of slashers they thought they'd already put down. This epic collection sets the staus quo for Cass & Vlad's new adventures. Collects HACK/SLASH ANNUAL #2 and HACK/SLASH #1-4. Also includes the original six-page story "Night Funeral in Eminence."
name: Vol. 9

description: As the possessed, power-enhanced Hulk wreaks havoc through the countryside, only one group stands between him and untold destruction: The Vampire Nation! Dracula gathers the newly-united vampire legions to stop the unstoppable, but as volley after volley fails, it appears their only hope may be a mysterious stranger from Dracula‚Äôs past. Marvel craftsman Victor Gischler and artist-to-watch Ryan Stegman deliver a story with plenty of bite, and they aren‚Äôt afraid to draw blood!
name: Hulk VS. Dracula, Part 1

description: Giselle learns the hard way that the palace can be just as dangerous as the streets in this exciting second‚Ä®installment of the relaunched Crossgen classic. Facing upheaval in the heavens as Verne's moons continue to drift apart, and unrest in the city as revolution brews, Giselle must find her place among Master Alexander's new apprentices--and stay ahead of the lovely Felice's vicious plots. Meanwhile, Genevieve finds herself the unwitting new protege of a charismatic revolutionary...and her destiny takes an unexpected turn.
name: Celestial Revolutions
